00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:01,370
 This is the news. 

247
00:26:01,370 --> 00:26:06,300
 President Heo Jung Se is announcing several measures to strengthen law and order. 

248
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:10,310
 He said he is fully aware of the results from the live court show started earlier this year... 

249
00:26:10,310 --> 00:26:12,050
Let me check your bag.

250
00:26:12,050 --> 00:26:14,170
 Police 

251
00:26:14,170 --> 00:26:17,410
- Spread your arms. 
 - Give it to me. 
 - I said spread your arms.

252
00:26:21,650 --> 00:26:24,360
The mood is unusual these days.

253
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:28,290
The higher-ups must have issued instructions  to take a firm stance.

254
00:26:28,290 --> 00:26:31,240
I don't know what's happening to this world.

255
00:26:33,630 --> 00:26:38,220
Judge Kim must not know because he doing important work.

256
00:26:38,220 --> 00:26:39,880
I'm the only fool here.

257
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:41,350
Judge Oh, that—

258
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:43,110
Forget it.

259
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:51,310
 In order to make the strict punitive measures taken by the live court  

260
00:26:51,310 --> 00:26:55,730
  mandatory to the general courts nationwide, they have decided to make the sentencing standards more stringent on one hand 

261
00:26:55,730 --> 00:26:58,960
  and set up an operational support group   

262
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:02,130
  to actively support and promote the live court. 

263
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:04,700
Who is it? 
  Chief Judge Kang Yo Han 

264
00:27:09,490 --> 00:27:12,030
Hello, Young Master.

265
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:24,120
Are you crazy?

266
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:26,350
How dare you come here as you please?

267
00:27:26,350 --> 00:27:28,190
Nice to meet you.

268
00:27:28,190 --> 00:27:33,340
I'm Jeong Seon Ah, I will be serving as the head of the Operational Support Group for the live court.

269
00:27:33,340 --> 00:27:37,320
I look forward to your kind cooperation, Judge Kang Yo Han.

270
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:51,650
This is a violation of judicial independence.

271
00:27:51,650 --> 00:27:54,190
Are you saying that judges whose sentences are beneath the new sentencing standards

272
00:27:54,190 --> 00:27:57,290
and those who have a higher rate of dismissing warrants will be punished?

273
00:27:57,290 --> 00:28:01,620
The Blue House is building social discipline, so the judicial branch should cooperate.

274
00:28:01,620 --> 00:28:04,560
Is it for the judiciary to cooperate with the Blue House?

275
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:09,750
Without a nation, there is no judicial independence.

276
00:28:09,750 --> 00:28:12,090
Judicial independence is necessary

277
00:28:12,090 --> 00:28:16,290
in order for a nation to exist, Chief Justice!

278
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:26,930
Was being the director of the foundation not enough?

279
00:28:26,930 --> 00:28:32,690
That's funny. Someone like you is going to be supporting me?

280
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:37,100
That hurts my feelings. I'm being sincere.

281
00:28:38,470 --> 00:28:40,690
- Sincere? 
 - Of course.

282
00:28:40,690 --> 00:28:42,990
I owe you my life, Young Master.

283
00:28:42,990 --> 00:28:47,700
I messed with your sheep farm, so you could steal that spot.

284
00:28:47,700 --> 00:28:50,160
Is that it?

285
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:53,960
Yes, I appreciated that, but there's much more to it.

286
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:59,550
It was at your house that I saw a beautiful world for the first time in my life.

287
00:28:59,550 --> 00:29:02,260
Everything there was shining.

288
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:05,070
I lived so I could go back there.

289
00:29:05,070 --> 00:29:08,520
Not as a petty thief, but as an owner.

290
00:29:09,490 --> 00:29:14,120
As owner of the world you had me kicked out of.

291
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:16,320
You haven't changed at all.

292
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:21,020
You're just the same hungry petty thief.

293
00:29:21,020 --> 00:29:26,270
A petty thief who doesn't even know how broken she is.

294
00:29:31,830 --> 00:29:39,190
I love it when you're like this.

295
00:29:39,190 --> 00:29:46,460
When you laugh at me, swear at me, hurt me. It's exhilarating.

296
00:29:46,460 --> 00:29:51,690
That's why I want to harass you too.

297
00:29:51,690 --> 00:29:57,730
Scratch you, bite you, and pick at you.

298
00:30:01,390 --> 00:30:06,890
You still don't know me. I don't have much patience.

299
00:30:12,610 --> 00:30:15,410
I don't discriminate between men and women.

300
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:21,360
I...

301
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:30,750
treat them the same way.

302
00:30:33,870 --> 00:30:37,390
You and I are very similar.

303
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:41,410
Is that why you like me?

304
00:30:41,410 --> 00:30:43,110
Yes.

305
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:46,270
How much do you like me?

306
00:30:50,860 --> 00:30:53,230
I asked how much you liked me.

307
00:31:03,540 --> 00:31:05,490
 DIKE 

308
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:12,330
What are you doing?!

309
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:16,630
Are you all right?

310
00:31:16,630 --> 00:31:20,330
I'm all right. You saved my life.

311
00:31:20,900 --> 00:31:23,130
Oh ... yes.

312
00:31:25,890 --> 00:31:28,200
Chief, what is this—

313
00:31:29,230 --> 00:31:33,170
Then that's all for today. I'll see you again.

314
00:31:48,020 --> 00:31:52,450
That woman is the head of the operational support group for the live court.

315
00:31:52,450 --> 00:31:54,460
Director Jeong is?

316
00:31:57,490 --> 00:31:59,230
Hello, Director Jeong.

317
00:31:59,230 --> 00:32:03,780
Judge Oh, we'll have meet in private soon, in a cozy setting.

318
00:32:08,290 --> 00:32:10,960
What is this?!

319
00:32:18,730 --> 00:32:24,200
- Chief, am I not a member of this court too? 
 - What are you talking about, all of the sudden?

320
00:32:24,200 --> 00:32:28,660
The whole country is in a state of turmoil over what you started, and you're not telling me anything.

321
00:32:28,660 --> 00:32:30,690
You said you'd resign, without a word of discussion between us.

322
00:32:30,690 --> 00:32:33,120
You said you would accept tips from all the citizens.

323
00:32:33,120 --> 00:32:35,960
Why is that woman suddenly showing up here again?

324
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:39,650
- Judge Oh. 
 - Just a moment, let me say one more thing.

325
00:32:41,900 --> 00:32:45,060
I don't know what you think of me,

326
00:32:45,060 --> 00:32:48,670
but I'm also a judge in this country and a member of this live court.

327
00:32:48,670 --> 00:32:51,270
If you're going to be like this, then do the trials by yourself.

328
00:32:51,270 --> 00:32:53,600
You've changed, Judge Oh.

329
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:56,090
"If you include me in the live court,

330
00:32:56,090 --> 00:32:59,830
I will be honored to just sit next to you for the rest of my life."

331
00:32:59,830 --> 00:33:02,720
Didn't you say this? That's what I remember.

332
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:05,020
You're become quite ambitious.

333
00:33:05,020 --> 00:33:08,960
It's something to celebrate, but I'm wondering what brought the change?

334
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:12,530
I've told you everything I have to say.

335
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,820
Is this how you do it?

336
00:33:26,820 --> 00:33:30,360
How are you going to fight the people who move the world

337
00:33:30,360 --> 00:33:33,940
by alienating the people right next to you? If you isolate yourself?

338
00:33:35,590 --> 00:33:37,690
Let's talk about that later.

339
00:33:39,190 --> 00:33:44,700
Stop by the house. Elijah seemed to be restless.

340
00:33:47,420 --> 00:33:51,780
Things are proceeding while I'm being completely excluded.

341
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:59,380
Seo Jeong Hak suddenly died, and now a violent organization is suddenly involved?

342
00:33:59,380 --> 00:34:01,740
Did we get information about that captured member?

343
00:34:01,740 --> 00:34:05,730
The National Intelligence Service is revealing nothing, saying that it is their jurisdiction.

344
00:34:05,730 --> 00:34:09,050
These dogs and pigs ...

345
00:34:09,050 --> 00:34:12,450
They are only taking orders from the president, huh?

346
00:34:16,030 --> 00:34:19,510
We have a team that's gathering dirt on Heo Jung Se's personal corruption, don't we?

347
00:34:19,510 --> 00:34:22,370
- Yes, Minister. 
 - A part of that team will need to be assigned elsewhere.

348
00:34:22,370 --> 00:34:25,120
Where do you mean?

349
00:34:27,690 --> 00:34:32,260
Jeong Seon Ah, the new chairwoman of the Social Responsibility Foundation.

350
00:34:32,990 --> 00:34:36,290
It appears that that vixen

351
00:34:36,290 --> 00:34:40,220
has latched onto the president.

352
00:34:58,180 --> 00:35:00,110
How about talking over a cup of coffee?

353
00:35:00,110 --> 00:35:02,100
Yes, it sounds good.

354
00:35:03,300 --> 00:35:05,120
Elijah.

355
00:35:18,350 --> 00:35:21,420
You seemed to question why I didn't include Oh Jin Ju.

356
00:35:21,420 --> 00:35:24,430
A panel of judges consists of three so that two can have the majority.

357
00:35:24,430 --> 00:35:26,560
Are you saying you don't need the minority?

358
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:30,160
But Judge Oh is a good person.

359
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:35,020
I don't believe in fickle things like 'belief in good faith.'

360
00:35:36,790 --> 00:35:41,330
So the only things you are interested in are resentment and rage, huh?

361
00:35:41,330 --> 00:35:43,200
At the very least.

362
00:35:44,300 --> 00:35:46,030
Cha Gyeong Hui's sponsor, her son...

363
00:35:46,030 --> 00:35:50,650
The reason that you've obsessively targeted Cha Gyeong Hui from the first trial,

364
00:35:50,650 --> 00:35:55,020
is it because of that? Because of Elijah?

365
00:36:01,950 --> 00:36:05,630
It's not such a simple matter.

366
00:36:05,630 --> 00:36:11,620
As I told you before, when those who rule the world band together, there is no way to defeat them.

367
00:36:12,260 --> 00:36:15,200
So you begin by isolating the strongest enemy.

368
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:18,650
Also the one that is easiest to isolate.

369
00:36:18,650 --> 00:36:20,040
Easy?

370
00:36:20,040 --> 00:36:22,560
Do you know why Cha Gyeong Hui is so strong?

371
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:24,580
Because she has everyone's weakness in her hands.

372
00:36:24,580 --> 00:36:28,600
If she is cornered, there will be many people who will be happy.

373
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:35,490
And I covet very much the weaknesses that Cha Gyeong Hui is holding.

374
00:36:36,430 --> 00:36:38,570
So you are saying that you will corner her further.

375
00:36:38,570 --> 00:36:42,990
Until Cha Gyeong Hui tries to use her final card to make a deal.

376
00:36:42,990 --> 00:36:47,120
If you understand, begin by examining this.

377
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:49,820
A list of cases that can be tried in the live court show.

378
00:36:49,820 --> 00:36:54,990
The show must go on.  The support of the public is our only weapon.

379
00:37:01,900 --> 00:37:07,290
But, about Do Yeong Chun ... Who exactly  is behind that?

380
00:37:07,290 --> 00:37:11,440
I can't say.  I am still looking into that.

381
00:37:11,440 --> 00:37:14,770
Whoever that may be, why do you think he did that?

382
00:37:14,770 --> 00:37:19,770
He's not a political criminal or worthy of negotiation with another country, so why?

383
00:37:19,770 --> 00:37:24,590
If we cannot find a specific reason, it's usually money.

384
00:37:24,590 --> 00:37:30,220
- Money? 
 - Money is a very powerful motive. To anyone.

385
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:41,760
Must we involve Judge Kim Ga On?

386
00:37:43,020 --> 00:37:45,630
- Why go to this length— 
 - Like it or not,

387
00:37:45,630 --> 00:37:48,960
I can't let an enemy remain immediately behind me.

388
00:37:51,100 --> 00:37:53,170
Either I must  make him join my side,

389
00:37:53,170 --> 00:37:54,570
  Or... 

390
00:37:54,570 --> 00:37:58,590
I must get rid of him, the element of risk.

391
00:38:05,860 --> 00:38:07,740
Elijah?

392
00:38:09,530 --> 00:38:11,550
Come in.

393
00:38:16,590 --> 00:38:19,690
Eating frozen food again when I'm not here?

394
00:38:21,110 --> 00:38:24,530
What did you two talk about for so long?

395
00:38:24,530 --> 00:38:28,820
Just boring work stuff. Can I sit down?

396
00:38:28,820 --> 00:38:30,670
Sit down.

397
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:35,800
Of course, there is no way two ajeossis would talk about anything fun.

398
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:39,130
You're too much. I thought I was your oppa, not an ajeossi.

399
00:38:39,130 --> 00:38:45,090
Never mind. Why don't you come home to this house lately?

400
00:38:45,090 --> 00:38:49,960
Just... I've got a lot on my mind.

401
00:38:52,770 --> 00:38:57,760
I thought a bit about what you said to me last time.

402
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:59,200
What was that?

403
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:03,760
That awful scammer who made your parents die.

404
00:39:03,760 --> 00:39:06,130
I shouldn't have told you that. Don't be concerned about that.

405
00:39:06,130 --> 00:39:08,270
How could I not be concerned about that?

406
00:39:08,270 --> 00:39:12,400
I heard that you tried to kill yourself a number of times because of that punk!

407
00:39:12,400 --> 00:39:14,170
Elijah?

408
00:39:15,950 --> 00:39:17,930
- Let's kill him. 
 - What?

409
00:39:17,930 --> 00:39:20,870
I thought about it a lot, and I think that would be best.

410
00:39:20,870 --> 00:39:24,030
I just can't understand why our citizens' taxes

411
00:39:24,030 --> 00:39:27,400
should be spent on giving a guy like that shelter, clothing, and three meals a day.

412
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:31,370
Can you even sleep? If I were you, I would feel so enraged that I could never get a decent night's sleep.

413
00:39:31,370 --> 00:39:35,290
So I thought about it

414
00:39:35,290 --> 00:39:37,740
and I don't think it's all that impossible.

415
00:39:37,740 --> 00:39:41,970
I will hack into the prison system and find out the days he can leave prison

416
00:39:41,970 --> 00:39:44,660
and then we hide, then we pounce on him...

417
00:39:44,660 --> 00:39:47,100
- Elijah. 
 - Hmm?

418
00:39:49,660 --> 00:39:53,400
Thank you for giving it so much thought.

419
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,830
No, I, just...

420
00:39:55,830 --> 00:39:59,590
But I'm really fine now. Don't be so concerned.

421
00:40:02,210 --> 00:40:05,790
Is that so? Then, well...

422
00:40:08,390 --> 00:40:10,700
What if...

423
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:17,300
This is just an absurd stretch of imagination ...

424
00:40:17,870 --> 00:40:22,440
What if someone made a complete switch of that bad guy? How would that be?

425
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:24,670
With some random person?

426
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:30,990
What? You've even imagined such an absurd thing?

427
00:40:30,990 --> 00:40:34,980
Instead of having such useless thoughts, it would be better to just kill him—

428
00:40:34,980 --> 00:40:38,470
I know, right? It's nonsense, isn't it?

429
00:40:38,470 --> 00:40:43,780
Right. Who would do such a crazy thing?

430
00:40:43,780 --> 00:40:45,140
And for what?

431
00:40:45,140 --> 00:40:47,000
Right?

432
00:40:47,930 --> 00:40:53,560
Unless it were a strange person with a strange purpose, why would anyone?

433
00:40:55,830 --> 00:40:59,790
Never mind. Rest well, Elijah.

434
00:41:01,070 --> 00:41:03,230
Sleep well, Elijah.

435
00:41:07,710 --> 00:41:10,030
What's with him?

436
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:26,720
 Metropolitan Investigation Unit 
 Inspector Yun Su Hyeon 

437
00:41:43,690 --> 00:41:45,250
I was surprised.

438
00:41:45,250 --> 00:41:49,680
I had been thinking of you a lot, Elijah. Then you called me.

439
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:54,430
Well, I didn't think it would be helpful to come here with the ajeossis.

440
00:41:54,430 --> 00:41:56,040
That one.

441
00:42:02,540 --> 00:42:05,090
- How do you like this one? 
 - Very pretty, suits you well.

442
00:42:05,090 --> 00:42:07,410
Well, I am a good model.

443
00:42:11,270 --> 00:42:12,820
How about that one?

444
00:42:12,820 --> 00:42:15,680
This one looks a bit old-fashioned...

445
00:42:15,680 --> 00:42:19,440
I mean, rather, it looks very adult.

446
00:42:22,790 --> 00:42:24,360
Is that right?

447
00:42:26,310 --> 00:42:32,150
So is something going on with Ga On lately?

448
00:42:32,150 --> 00:42:36,170
Ga On? Who knows?

449
00:42:36,940 --> 00:42:40,130
What? You said you two were best friends.

450
00:42:40,130 --> 00:42:41,640
Are you worried for him?

451
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:45,700
Worry? Why would I?

452
00:42:45,700 --> 00:42:48,700
- Please wrap this one up. 
  - Yes.

453
00:42:48,760 --> 00:42:50,990
Also the one that this ajumma was looking at earlier.

454
00:42:50,990 --> 00:42:52,690
Yes? Ah...

455
00:42:52,690 --> 00:42:57,470
'Ajumma?' No, it's fine, I don't need it.

456
00:42:57,470 --> 00:43:00,460
Then why don't you pick something out for yourself?

457
00:43:00,460 --> 00:43:03,060
It's no fun if I'm shopping by myself.

458
00:43:03,660 --> 00:43:05,770
That sounds good too,

459
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:09,820
but how about if we visit somewhere else?

460
00:43:09,820 --> 00:43:11,320
Somewhere else?

461
00:44:06,590 --> 00:44:08,270
So you like him, don't you?

462
00:44:09,930 --> 00:44:11,980
Ice cream?

463
00:44:11,980 --> 00:44:13,730
You know what I mean.

464
00:44:14,350 --> 00:44:16,530
Ga On?

465
00:44:16,530 --> 00:44:19,780
Well, I can't say that I don't.

466
00:44:19,780 --> 00:44:23,560
After all, I have a history of having confessed my love to him five times since kindergarten.

467
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:27,530
- Five times? 
 - And I was rejected every single time.

468
00:44:29,070 --> 00:44:30,390
So why... ?

469
00:44:30,390 --> 00:44:33,150
So why did I keep on confessing?

470
00:44:33,150 --> 00:44:35,820
Right, why did I do that?

471
00:44:35,820 --> 00:44:40,460
Well, it all began with his face, of course. He was very cute in the past.

472
00:44:40,460 --> 00:44:41,560
And?

473
00:44:41,560 --> 00:44:45,410
But... he cried.

474
00:44:45,410 --> 00:44:46,770
Pardon?

475
00:44:48,250 --> 00:44:52,490
That was the first time his family was majorly ruined.

476
00:44:52,490 --> 00:44:55,300
So he had to quit kindergarten.

477
00:44:56,750 --> 00:45:00,090
So he cried. He bawled.

478
00:45:00,090 --> 00:45:02,970
And I hated seeing that so much.

479
00:45:03,650 --> 00:45:09,390
I hated that he was crying, and I couldn't do anything for him.

480
00:45:10,250 --> 00:45:15,070
So before I realized it, I ended up... confessing...

481
00:45:17,090 --> 00:45:18,860
I was an idiot, huh?

482
00:45:20,940 --> 00:45:24,450
Don't tell me that ... every time he cried...

483
00:45:26,440 --> 00:45:32,450
Yes, I ended up seeing Ga On cry as many as five times.

484
00:45:45,980 --> 00:45:51,020
Perhaps a cloud of misfortune entered his home.

485
00:45:51,990 --> 00:45:54,440
It never stopped.

486
00:45:55,330 --> 00:45:57,160
And just kept coming...

487
00:46:04,830 --> 00:46:07,810
It's very late. Shall we get going now?

488
00:46:07,810 --> 00:46:09,390
Eonni,

489
00:46:15,140 --> 00:46:16,960
let's go together.

490
00:46:19,710 --> 00:46:21,910
Yes, Elijah.

491
00:46:29,790 --> 00:46:31,740
Yes, it's me.

492
00:46:31,740 --> 00:46:35,030
You once investigated Jung Won F &amp; B, didn't you?

493
00:46:35,030 --> 00:46:38,920
Yes, can you get me a few years' worth of their financial records?

494
00:46:38,920 --> 00:46:40,510
Yes, thanks.

495
00:46:43,440 --> 00:46:44,960
Ga On.

496
00:46:46,330 --> 00:46:50,360
Sorry for being late when you must be so busy, Prosecutor Park.

497
00:46:50,360 --> 00:46:55,540
I should come running when asked by Judge Kim Ga On, the most successful among my law school classmates.

498
00:46:55,540 --> 00:46:59,250
- I'm successful? 
 - Of course. You are a star.

499
00:47:00,190 --> 00:47:04,690
Give me your autograph here, so I can give it to my nephew.

500
00:47:04,690 --> 00:47:06,240
Sure.

501
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:09,770
Actually, I have a request for you.

502
00:47:09,770 --> 00:47:11,760
What is it?

503
00:47:11,800 --> 00:47:15,000
There's a prisoner currently serving his sentence. He stole several hundreds of billions won.

504
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:18,020
I think the Seizure of the Proceeds of Crime Team was under the Prosecutor's Office at the time.

505
00:47:18,100 --> 00:47:22,400
I know it's quite a difficult task but could you find out for me whether they actually seized anything?

506
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:24,590
Is the Live Court Show working on something related to that?

507
00:47:24,590 --> 00:47:27,390
No, no. This is a personal matter.

508
00:47:27,390 --> 00:47:29,360
I would really appreciate it if you can help me.

509
00:47:30,370 --> 00:47:32,450
I understand.

510
00:47:32,450 --> 00:47:36,990
But in return, you need to give a lot more autographs.

511
00:47:36,990 --> 00:47:39,580
This won't be enough.

512
00:47:39,580 --> 00:47:41,800
Sure. Thanks.

513
00:47:46,290 --> 00:47:47,780
You're home?

514
00:47:48,850 --> 00:47:50,540
Have you come back for good now?

515
00:47:50,540 --> 00:47:54,310
Actually no, but I need to take care of these.

516
00:47:54,310 --> 00:47:57,910
You shouldn't visit, you should return completely. This is your home.

517
00:47:57,910 --> 00:48:00,950
But there are people I need to take care of over there, too.

518
00:48:02,580 --> 00:48:05,460
How about taking care of yourself? Please.

519
00:48:05,460 --> 00:48:07,630
Me? What about?

520
00:48:07,630 --> 00:48:10,710
Why do I need any care? I'm living an exceedingly comfortable life as it is.

521
00:48:15,880 --> 00:48:17,230
- Su Hyeon? 
 - Yes?

522
00:48:17,230 --> 00:48:20,740
- What are you thinking of so intently? 
 - Well, just...

523
00:48:21,700 --> 00:48:23,720
You know, Ga On ...

524
00:48:23,720 --> 00:48:25,240
Professor.

525
00:48:30,610 --> 00:48:34,650
- You're here. 
 - Why does this house have so many stairs?

526
00:48:34,650 --> 00:48:36,460
Oh my legs.

527
00:48:36,460 --> 00:48:39,460
But what brings you here so late?

528
00:48:45,220 --> 00:48:47,400
Did you enjoy the food?

529
00:48:48,180 --> 00:48:49,570
Why orange juice?

530
00:48:49,570 --> 00:48:52,390
You shouldn't bring orange juice. You should bring soju.

531
00:48:52,390 --> 00:48:56,440
Of course he should have. Not a sensible guy, is he?

532
00:48:57,920 --> 00:49:01,550
I called Su Hyeon after a long while to ask how she's doing, and she said you would be here.

533
00:49:01,550 --> 00:49:05,690
We work together at the Supreme Court every day. You didn't need to go out of your way to see me.

534
00:49:05,690 --> 00:49:11,070
These days, I have no idea if the place we work at is an actual court of law or not.

535
00:49:11,070 --> 00:49:14,790
I met with the chief justice today, and he was more like a military commander.

536
00:49:14,790 --> 00:49:17,210
He said that all the courts in our nation need to get in shipshape line.

537
00:49:17,210 --> 00:49:21,240
This kind of nation is not what I fought for in the streets during my youth.

538
00:49:21,240 --> 00:49:23,800
We received an order to carry live ammunition.

539
00:49:23,800 --> 00:49:27,660
I didn't become a police officer to point a gun at our citizens' chests.

540
00:49:28,300 --> 00:49:30,660
Police brutality is growing worse.

541
00:49:30,660 --> 00:49:33,090
If a drunkard makes some noise, the police batons—

542
00:49:33,090 --> 00:49:36,020
But is that really so wrong?

543
00:49:36,020 --> 00:49:37,700
Ga On.

544
00:49:38,680 --> 00:49:44,600
It's not right for police officers to get beat up by drunkards every night either. Is that a proper country?

545
00:49:44,600 --> 00:49:50,170
But once you wake a monster and it erupts, it becomes uncontrollable.

546
00:49:50,170 --> 00:49:53,420
And your Live Court Show is what woke that monster.

547
00:49:54,280 --> 00:49:55,870
So what do you plan to do about it?

548
00:49:55,870 --> 00:49:58,190
I will get rid of your court.

549
00:49:58,190 --> 00:50:00,340
Using internal channels in the judiciary is now useless.

550
00:50:00,340 --> 00:50:04,330
So I will present this problem using citizens' groups and, once it's reported by media companies with a conscience,

551
00:50:04,330 --> 00:50:07,140
it will trigger a parliamentary investigation by the opposition party. That's the plan.

552
00:50:07,140 --> 00:50:08,650
Ga On.

553
00:50:10,150 --> 00:50:12,350
You are the key to that plan.

554
00:50:12,350 --> 00:50:16,990
What you've seen, heard, and learned, we need all of it.

555
00:50:16,990 --> 00:50:19,900
- Is this a notice? 
 - It's a request.

556
00:50:19,900 --> 00:50:23,560
And... I'm sorry.

557
00:50:28,100 --> 00:50:30,260
I deserve to die.

558
00:50:33,420 --> 00:50:36,870
 Associate Judge Kim Ga On 

559
00:50:50,680 --> 00:50:51,900
Yes?

560
00:50:51,900 --> 00:50:53,940
Can you come see me?

561
00:51:01,610 --> 00:51:03,580
Did you look into it?

562
00:51:04,510 --> 00:51:06,030
What do you mean?

563
00:51:06,030 --> 00:51:09,790
What I gave you, the next trial cases.

564
00:51:09,790 --> 00:51:11,800
Yes.

565
00:51:13,120 --> 00:51:15,640
You still have a lot on your mind.

566
00:51:18,550 --> 00:51:21,020
We're going to go somewhere together later.

567
00:51:22,730 --> 00:51:24,060
Where else are we going again?

568
00:51:24,060 --> 00:51:26,190
I need to show you something.

569
00:51:37,570 --> 00:51:39,700
Where are we going?

570
00:51:42,150 --> 00:51:44,520
I asked where we are going?

571
00:51:46,600 --> 00:51:48,940
You're here.

572
00:51:48,940 --> 00:51:51,580
This is a friend who helps me with my work.

573
00:51:51,580 --> 00:51:53,760
And this is Judge Kim Ga On.

574
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:55,960
Nice to meet you.

575
00:51:56,800 --> 00:51:59,370
You must be the one who did the meticulous background check on me.

576
00:51:59,370 --> 00:52:01,240
Your skills are impressive.

577
00:52:01,240 --> 00:52:05,130
Judge Kim was working hard too, on Judge Kang Yo Han's background check.

578
00:52:05,130 --> 00:52:08,000
I'm sorry, but I don't think I can give you a compliment.

579
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:10,020
Your skills weren't that great.

580
00:52:10,020 --> 00:52:14,080
I'm sorry, my specialty isn't that kind of job.

581
00:52:14,100 --> 00:52:18,300
You two look heartwarming, but that is enough for your introductions.

582
00:52:18,340 --> 00:52:22,060
Is he what you wanted to show me?

583
00:52:23,000 --> 00:52:24,970
You once asked me this.

584
00:52:24,970 --> 00:52:28,790
How am I going to fight against the people who control the world?

585
00:52:28,790 --> 00:52:31,020
Well, I would say the answer is

586
00:52:31,020 --> 00:52:34,680
making sure of the win even before the game starts.

587
00:52:34,680 --> 00:52:36,820
How is that possible?

588
00:52:36,820 --> 00:52:39,330
Of course, it's not easy to do it on my own.

589
00:52:39,330 --> 00:52:43,710
That's why there are people who help me besides this guy. Here and there.

590
00:52:43,710 --> 00:52:45,640
Are you saying you have assistants?

591
00:52:45,640 --> 00:52:48,120
It's time for them to arrive.

592
00:52:51,320 --> 00:52:53,280
Lawyer Go.

593
00:53:04,770 --> 00:53:06,490
 I'm going to meet the lawyer today. 

594
00:53:06,490 --> 00:53:07,710
 Chairman. 

595
00:53:07,710 --> 00:53:10,290
 Do you admit negligence in your work? 

596
00:53:10,290 --> 00:53:13,040
 Attorney Go, you said five years. 

597
00:53:13,040 --> 00:53:14,780
 Five years. 

598
00:53:18,220 --> 00:53:20,580
Jang Gi Hyeon wasn't the only you bribed?

599
00:53:20,580 --> 00:53:25,940
I told you, the win must be certain even before the game starts.

600
00:53:25,940 --> 00:53:30,420
Judge Kim, I have a lot to apologize for from the last time.

601
00:53:30,420 --> 00:53:33,650
Then Lee Yeong Min's trial... That was impossible, how could you possibly ...?

602
00:53:33,650 --> 00:53:35,920
You're right, that was too much.

603
00:53:35,920 --> 00:53:39,030
But still, couldn't I at least stir the embers?

604
00:53:39,030 --> 00:53:42,970
- The embers? 
 - It's hard to open the sluice gate at the start.

605
00:53:42,970 --> 00:53:46,170
An aspiring actress. I like her tone.

606
00:53:46,170 --> 00:53:50,030
Nice to meet you. I'm a fan. I even joined your fan club.

